+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T62Ms7UHn3bZxT7KHZbre3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have now read every single file in the codebase. Here is the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Full Codebase Analysis: SSG Toolkit\n\n### 1. Project Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n  .eslintrc.cjs               -- ESLint config (TS parser, recommended rules)\n  .gitignore                   -- ignores node_modules/ and dist/\n  package.json                 -- project manifest\n  package-lock.json            -- dependency lock\n  tsconfig.json                -- TypeScript config\n  vitest.config.ts             -- Vitest config (globals: true, 10s timeout)\n  TASK.md                      -- Task requirements\n  src/\n    core/\n      types.ts                 -- All type interfaces\n      engine.ts                -- BuildEngine class\n      templates.ts             -- Default and List templates\n      index.ts                 -- Barrel re-export\n    plugins/\n      .gitkeep                 -- Empty directory (plugins must be created here)\n  tests/\n    core.test.ts               -- 15 core engine tests\n    plugins/\n      markdown-ext.test.ts     -- 8 tests\n      asset-pipeline.test.ts   -- 8 tests\n      syntax-highlight.test.ts -- 8 tests\n      taxonomy.test.ts         -- 8 tests\n      rss-feed.test.ts         -- 7 tests\n      search-index.test.ts     -- 7 tests\n      sitemap.test.ts          -- 7 tests\n      dev-server.test.ts       -- 7 tests\n```\n\nTotal: 15 existing core tests + 60 plugin tests = 75 tests.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Plugin Interface (`/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\n**`SiteConfig`** -- Site-level configuration:\n- `title: string` -- site title\n- `baseUrl: string` -- e.g. `\"https://example.com\"`\n- `outputDir: string` -- output directory path\n- `contentDir: string` -- content source directory\n- `templateDir: string` -- template directory\n\n**`ContentFile`** -- Represents one content file:\n- `slug: string` -- URL slug (e.g. `\"my-post\"`)\n- `title: string` -- document title\n- `content: string` -- raw content (markdown or HTML)\n- `metadata: Record<string, unknown>` -- arbitrary key-value metadata\n- `date?: string` -- optional date string\n- `tags?: string[]` -- optional tag array\n- `template?: string` -- optional template name override\n\n**`BuildContext`** -- Shared state passed through the build pipeline:\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- site configuration\n- `files: ContentFile[]` -- all content files\n- `output: Map<string, string>` -- output path to rendered content mapping\n- `assets: Map<string, Buffer>` -- output path to binary data mapping\n- `data: Map<string, unknown>` -- shared plugin data store (plugins communicate here)\n\n**`PluginHooks`** -- Three lifecycle hooks (all optional):\n- `beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs before content transformation\n- `transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile` -- transforms each file individually\n- `afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs after template rendering\n\n**`Plugin`** -- The plugin interface each plugin must implement:\n- `name: string` -- unique plugin identifier\n- `version: string` -- semver version\n- `dependencies: string[]` -- names of plugins this depends on (for topological sort)\n- `hooks: PluginHooks` -- the lifecycle hooks object\n\n**`Template`** -- Rendering template:\n- `name: string` -- template name (e.g. `\"default\"`, `\"list\"`)\n- `render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string` -- render function\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\n**`BuildEngine` class** -- Constructor takes `SiteConfig`. Key members:\n\n- **`registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)`** -- pushes plugin to internal array\n- **`registerTemplate(template: Template)`** -- stores template by name in a Map\n- **`resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]`** -- Topological sort using DFS:\n  - Builds a `pluginMap` (name -> Plugin)\n  - Uses `visited` (fully processed) and `visiting` (currently in DFS stack) sets\n  - Throws `\"Circular dependency detected: ${name}\"` if a node is re-entered during DFS\n  - Throws `\"Missing dependency: ${name} requires ${dep}\"` if a dependency is not registered\n  - Returns sorted array with dependencies before dependents\n\n- **`async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>`** -- The main build pipeline:\n  1. Creates a fresh `BuildContext` with shallow-copied files\n  2. Calls `resolvePluginOrder()` to get sorted plugins\n  3. **Phase 1: `beforeBuild`** -- Iterates sorted plugins, calls `beforeBuild(ctx)` if defined\n  4. **Phase 2: `transformContent`** -- For each sorted plugin with `transformContent`, iterates ALL files and replaces `ctx.files` with transformed versions\n  5. **Phase 3: Template rendering** -- For each file, looks up `file.template || 'default'` in templates map. If found, calls `template.render(file.content, {...data})` and stores in `ctx.output` as `\"${file.slug}.html\"`. If no template found, stores raw `file.content`.\n  6. **Phase 4: `afterBuild`** -- Iterates sorted plugins, calls `afterBuild(ctx)` if defined\n  7. Returns the `BuildContext`\n\n- **`getPlugins()`** -- returns copy of plugins array\n- **`getTemplates()`** -- returns copy of templates map\n\n**Key insight**: Template rendering passes these data fields: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, all of `...file.metadata`, `siteTitle` (from config.title), `baseUrl` (from config.baseUrl).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Template System (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\nTwo factory functions:\n\n**`createDefaultTemplate()`** -- Returns Template named `\"default\"`:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${data.title} | ${data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>${data.title}</h1>\n    ${data.date ? `<time>${data.date}</time>` : ''}\n    <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**`createListTemplate()`** -- Returns Template named `\"list\"`:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${data.title} | ${data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>${data.title}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**Barrel export** (`/workspace/src/core/index.ts`): exports `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types.\n\n---\n\n### 5. All 15 Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`)\n\nHelper functions: `makeFile()` creates a default `ContentFile`, `makePlugin()` creates a default `Plugin`. Both accept partial overrides. Uses `testConfig` with title `\"Test Site\"`, baseUrl `\"https://example.com\"`.\n\n1. **\"registers plugins\"** -- registerPlugin adds to getPlugins() list\n2. **\"registers templates\"** -- registerTemplate makes template available by name\n3. **\"builds with default template and renders HTML\"** -- verifies DOCTYPE, title, content, siteTitle in output\n4. **\"builds with list template and renders list HTML\"** -- verifies list template wraps in `<div class=\"list\">`\n5. **\"outputs raw content when no matching template\"** -- no template registered = raw content passthrough\n6. **\"calls plugin beforeBuild hook\"** -- confirms hook is invoked\n7. **\"calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files\"** -- `.toUpperCase()` transform verified\n8. **\"calls plugin afterBuild hook\"** -- confirms hook is invoked\n9. **\"executes plugins in dependency order\"** -- `b` depends on `a`; order is `[a, b]`\n10. **\"throws on circular dependency\"** -- `a->b->a` throws `\"Circular dependency\"`\n11. **\"throws on missing dependency\"** -- `a` requires `\"missing\"` throws `\"Missing dependency\"`\n12. **\"applies multiple plugins transformContent in order\"** -- `first` then `second` appending text\n13. **\"provides shared data store in build context\"** -- `ctx.data.set/get` works across hooks\n14. **\"retains file metadata through build\"** -- metadata, date, tags survive the build\n15. **\"produces empty output for empty file list\"** -- 0 files = 0 output entries\n\n---\n\n### 6. All Plugin Test Files (60 tests total)\n\n#### 6a. `markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests) -- imports `createMarkdownExtPlugin`\n\n1. **\"converts basic markdown to HTML\"** -- `# Hello` becomes `<h1>`, `**bold**` becomes `<strong>`\n2. **\"handles footnotes with [^1] syntax\"** -- `[^1]` inline becomes `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n3. **\"renders footnote section at bottom\"** -- `[^1]: text` becomes `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>`\n4. **\"converts :::note container to admonition div\"** -- `:::note\\n...\\n:::` becomes `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n5. **\"converts :::warning container\"** -- same pattern with `admonition-warning`\n6. **\"converts :::tip container\"** -- same pattern with `admonition-tip`\n7. **\"preserves existing HTML in content\"** -- already-HTML passes through\n8. **\"handles empty content\"** -- result.content is defined (not undefined/null)\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `transformContent` hook. No dependencies. Must use `marked` library for markdown conversion, plus custom footnote and admonition preprocessing.\n\n#### 6b. `asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests) -- imports `createAssetPipelinePlugin`\n\n1. **\"rewrites relative image URLs to /assets/ path\"** -- `src=\"./image.png\"` becomes `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n2. **\"rewrites relative link URLs\"** -- `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` becomes `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n3. **\"leaves absolute URLs unchanged\"** -- `https://` URLs untouched\n4. **\"generates asset manifest in ctx.data\"** -- `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `{ assets: ['photo.jpg'] }`\n5. **\"handles files with no asset references\"** -- content unchanged\n6. **\"handles multiple assets in one file\"** -- all three filenames in manifest\n7. **\"asset manifest includes all discovered assets\"** -- across multiple files, manifest accumulates\n8. **\"does not double-process already-rewritten URLs\"** -- `/assets/` prefixed URLs left alone, no manifest entry\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `transformContent` hook. No dependencies. Rewrites `src=\"./...\"` and `href=\"./...\"` to `/assets/...`. Stores manifest at `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` as `{ assets: string[] }`.\n\n#### 6c. `syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests) -- imports `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin`\n\n1. **\"adds language class to code blocks\"** -- `class=\"language-javascript\"` becomes `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n2. **\"adds data-language attribute to pre tags\"** -- `<pre>` gets `data-language=\"python\"`\n3. **\"handles multiple code blocks\"** -- both get `data-language`\n4. **\"handles code block with no language\"** -- `<pre><code>plain</code></pre>` unchanged, no `highlighted` class\n5. **\"adds highlighted class\"** -- confirms `highlighted` appears\n6. **\"preserves code block content\"** -- actual code text unchanged\n7. **\"handles empty code blocks\"** -- still gets `data-language` and `highlighted`\n8. **\"does not modify inline code\"** -- `<code>` not inside `<pre>` left alone\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `transformContent` hook. No dependencies. Operates on `<pre><code class=\"language-XXX\">` patterns: adds `highlighted` to class, adds `data-language=\"XXX\"` to `<pre>` tag.\n\n#### 6d. `taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests) -- imports `createTaxonomyPlugin`\n\n1. **\"builds tag index from file tags\"** -- `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` with proper counts\n2. **\"generates tag listing pages\"** -- `ctx.output.has('tags/javascript.html')` with post titles\n3. **\"handles files with no tags\"** -- tagMap.size is 0\n4. **\"handles files with multiple tags\"** -- all 3 tags present in map\n5. **\"tag pages list all files with that tag\"** -- both post titles in tag page HTML\n6. **\"stores tag map in ctx.data\"** -- `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true\n7. **\"handles empty file list\"** -- tagMap.size is 0\n8. **\"tags are case-normalized to lowercase\"** -- `JavaScript` and `JAVASCRIPT` both map to `javascript`\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `beforeBuild` (builds tag index into `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']` as `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`) and `afterBuild` (generates `tags/{tag}.html` pages into `ctx.output`). No dependencies. Case-normalizes tags to lowercase.\n\n#### 6e. `rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests) -- imports `createRssFeedPlugin`\n\n1. **\"generates valid RSS 2.0 XML\"** -- `feed.xml` with `<?xml`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`\n2. **\"feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown\"** -- wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n3. **\"feed items include category tags from taxonomy\"** -- reads `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`, outputs `<category>javascript</category>`\n4. **\"feed includes channel title from config\"** -- `<title>Test Site</title>`\n5. **\"feed items sorted by date newest first\"** -- descending date order\n6. **\"handles files without dates\"** -- title present, no `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>`\n7. **\"feed link uses baseUrl\"** -- `<link>https://example.com</link>` for channel, `<link>https://example.com/post-1.html</link>` for items\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `afterBuild`. Dependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`. Generates `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`. Reads `taxonomy-tags` from `ctx.data` for categories. Sorts items by date descending. Uses CDATA for content.\n\n#### 6f. `search-index.test.ts` (7 tests) -- imports `createSearchIndexPlugin`\n\n1. **\"generates search-index.json in ctx.output\"** -- output key exists\n2. **\"index entries have title, slug, and plain text content\"** -- strips HTML, includes `slug`, `title`, `content`\n3. **\"HTML tags stripped from indexed content\"** -- no `<` or `>` in content field\n4. **\"code blocks included in searchable text\"** -- `const x = 1;` present after stripping\n5. **\"handles empty file list\"** -- returns `[]`\n6. **\"search index is valid JSON\"** -- parses without error, is array, correct length\n7. **\"index entries include tags if present\"** -- `tags: ['js', 'web']` in index entry\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `afterBuild`. Dependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`. Generates `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`. Each entry: `{ slug, title, content (plain text, HTML stripped), tags? }`.\n\n#### 6g. `sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests) -- imports `createSitemapPlugin`\n\n1. **\"generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output\"** -- output key exists\n2. **\"includes all content page URLs\"** -- `https://example.com/post-1.html` for each output entry\n3. **\"includes taxonomy tag page URLs\"** -- reads `taxonomy-tags` from data, includes tag pages\n4. **\"includes feed.xml URL\"** -- if `feed.xml` is in output, it appears in sitemap\n5. **\"URLs use baseUrl from config\"** -- all URLs prefixed with config.baseUrl\n6. **\"sitemap is valid XML structure\"** -- `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`\n7. **\"handles site with no tag pages\"** -- no `/tags/` in sitemap when no taxonomy data\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `afterBuild`. Dependencies: `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`. Generates `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`. Iterates all keys in `ctx.output`, constructs full URLs with baseUrl. Valid XML with `<urlset>` wrapper.\n\n#### 6h. `dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests) -- imports `createDevServerPlugin`\n\n1. **\"stores dev-server-config in ctx.data\"** -- `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` is true\n2. **\"config includes port setting\"** -- port is a number\n3. **\"config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline\"** -- reads `ctx.data['asset-manifest']`, populates `assetPaths` and routes with `handler: 'asset'`\n4. **\"config includes search index path\"** -- if `search-index.json` in output, `searchIndexPath` is `'/search-index.json'`\n5. **\"config includes content routes\"** -- each `.html` output gets a route with `handler: 'static'`\n6. **\"default port is 3000\"** -- `config.port === 3000`\n7. **\"handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\"** -- `assetPaths` defaults to `[]`\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `afterBuild`. Dependencies: `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`. Stores config in `ctx.data['dev-server-config']` as:\n```typescript\n{\n  port: number;               // default 3000\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;  // 'static' for HTML, 'asset' for assets\n  assetPaths: string[];       // from asset-manifest\n  searchIndexPath: string;    // '/search-index.json' if present\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Package & Config Summary\n\n**`package.json`**:\n- Name: `bench-ssg-toolkit`, version `1.0.0`, type `\"module\"` (ESM)\n- Scripts: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint src/ tests/), `test` (vitest run)\n- Dependencies: `express@^5.2.1`, `marked@^17.0.2`, `@types/express@^5.0.6`, `@types/marked@^5.0.2`\n- DevDependencies: `typescript@^5.9.3`, `vitest@^2.1.9`, `eslint@^8.57.1`, `@typescript-eslint/*`\n\n**`tsconfig.json`**: strict mode, ES2022 target, Node16 module/moduleResolution, outDir `./dist`, rootDir `./src`, declaration enabled.\n\n**`vitest.config.ts`**: globals: true, testTimeout: 10000ms.\n\n**`.eslintrc.cjs`**: TS parser, recommended rules, unused vars ignored if prefixed with `_`.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Existing Plugins in `src/plugins/`\n\nThe directory contains only `.gitkeep` -- it is empty. All 8 plugins need to be created from scratch.\n\n---\n\n### Plugin Dependency DAG Summary\n\n```\nWave 1 (no deps):\n  markdown-ext        []\n  asset-pipeline      []\n  syntax-highlight    []\n  taxonomy            []\n\nWave 2 (depends on Wave 1):\n  rss-feed            ['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']\n  search-index        ['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']\n\nWave 3 (depends on Wave 2):\n  sitemap             ['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']\n  dev-server          ['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']\n```\n\nEach plugin exports a `createXxxPlugin()` factory function returning a `Plugin` object. The inter-plugin communication channel is `ctx.data` (a `Map<string, unknown>`), with these known keys:\n- `'taxonomy-tags'` -- `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` (written by taxonomy, read by rss-feed and sitemap)\n- `'asset-manifest'` -- `{ assets: string[] }` (written by asset-pipeline, read by dev-server)\n- `'dev-server-config'` -- `DevServerConfig` object (written by dev-server)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ada369b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36615\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 106624</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"149a2b1d-04e2-4369-8f92-eb13d6628038","uuid":"316edb9c-a32b-4fd4-a0bd-ff12c1414212","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore this Static Site Generator toolkit codebase. I need to understand:\n\n1. The full project structure (all files and directories)\n2. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts - every field and method\n3. The build engine in src/core/ - how it loads/runs plugins\n4. The template system\n5. All 15 existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n6. All plugin test files in tests/plugins/ - read every single one completely\n7. package.json - dependencies, scripts, tsconfig\n8. Any existing plugins in src/plugins/\n\nRead every file completely. This is critical context for building 8 plugins.","agentId":"ada369b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have now read every single file in the codebase. Here is the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Full Codebase Analysis: SSG Toolkit\n\n### 1. Project Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n  .eslintrc.cjs               -- ESLint config (TS parser, recommended rules)\n  .gitignore                   -- ignores node_modules/ and dist/\n  package.json                 -- project manifest\n  package-lock.json            -- dependency lock\n  tsconfig.json                -- TypeScript config\n  vitest.config.ts             -- Vitest config (globals: true, 10s timeout)\n  TASK.md                      -- Task requirements\n  src/\n    core/\n      types.ts                 -- All type interfaces\n      engine.ts                -- BuildEngine class\n      templates.ts             -- Default and List templates\n      index.ts                 -- Barrel re-export\n    plugins/\n      .gitkeep                 -- Empty directory (plugins must be created here)\n  tests/\n    core.test.ts               -- 15 core engine tests\n    plugins/\n      markdown-ext.test.ts     -- 8 tests\n      asset-pipeline.test.ts   -- 8 tests\n      syntax-highlight.test.ts -- 8 tests\n      taxonomy.test.ts         -- 8 tests\n      rss-feed.test.ts         -- 7 tests\n      search-index.test.ts     -- 7 tests\n      sitemap.test.ts          -- 7 tests\n      dev-server.test.ts       -- 7 tests\n```\n\nTotal: 15 existing core tests + 60 plugin tests = 75 tests.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Plugin Interface (`/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\n**`SiteConfig`** -- Site-level configuration:\n- `title: string` -- site title\n- `baseUrl: string` -- e.g. `\"https://example.com\"`\n- `outputDir: string` -- output directory path\n- `contentDir: string` -- content source directory\n- `templateDir: string` -- template directory\n\n**`ContentFile`** -- Represents one content file:\n- `slug: string` -- URL slug (e.g. `\"my-post\"`)\n- `title: string` -- document title\n- `content: string` -- raw content (markdown or HTML)\n- `metadata: Record<string, unknown>` -- arbitrary key-value metadata\n- `date?: string` -- optional date string\n- `tags?: string[]` -- optional tag array\n- `template?: string` -- optional template name override\n\n**`BuildContext`** -- Shared state passed through the build pipeline:\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- site configuration\n- `files: ContentFile[]` -- all content files\n- `output: Map<string, string>` -- output path to rendered content mapping\n- `assets: Map<string, Buffer>` -- output path to binary data mapping\n- `data: Map<string, unknown>` -- shared plugin data store (plugins communicate here)\n\n**`PluginHooks`** -- Three lifecycle hooks (all optional):\n- `beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs before content transformation\n- `transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile` -- transforms each file individually\n- `afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs after template rendering\n\n**`Plugin`** -- The plugin interface each plugin must implement:\n- `name: string` -- unique plugin identifier\n- `version: string` -- semver version\n- `dependencies: string[]` -- names of plugins this depends on (for topological sort)\n- `hooks: PluginHooks` -- the lifecycle hooks object\n\n**`Template`** -- Rendering template:\n- `name: string` -- template name (e.g. `\"default\"`, `\"list\"`)\n- `render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string` -- render function\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\n**`BuildEngine` class** -- Constructor takes `SiteConfig`. Key members:\n\n- **`registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)`** -- pushes plugin to internal array\n- **`registerTemplate(template: Template)`** -- stores template by name in a Map\n- **`resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]`** -- Topological sort using DFS:\n  - Builds a `pluginMap` (name -> Plugin)\n  - Uses `visited` (fully processed) and `visiting` (currently in DFS stack) sets\n  - Throws `\"Circular dependency detected: ${name}\"` if a node is re-entered during DFS\n  - Throws `\"Missing dependency: ${name} requires ${dep}\"` if a dependency is not registered\n  - Returns sorted array with dependencies before dependents\n\n- **`async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>`** -- The main build pipeline:\n  1. Creates a fresh `BuildContext` with shallow-copied files\n  2. Calls `resolvePluginOrder()` to get sorted plugins\n  3. **Phase 1: `beforeBuild`** -- Iterates sorted plugins, calls `beforeBuild(ctx)` if defined\n  4. **Phase 2: `transformContent`** -- For each sorted plugin with `transformContent`, iterates ALL files and replaces `ctx.files` with transformed versions\n  5. **Phase 3: Template rendering** -- For each file, looks up `file.template || 'default'` in templates map. If found, calls `template.render(file.content, {...data})` and stores in `ctx.output` as `\"${file.slug}.html\"`. If no template found, stores raw `file.content`.\n  6. **Phase 4: `afterBuild`** -- Iterates sorted plugins, calls `afterBuild(ctx)` if defined\n  7. Returns the `BuildContext`\n\n- **`getPlugins()`** -- returns copy of plugins array\n- **`getTemplates()`** -- returns copy of templates map\n\n**Key insight**: Template rendering passes these data fields: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, all of `...file.metadata`, `siteTitle` (from config.title), `baseUrl` (from config.baseUrl).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Template System (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\nTwo factory functions:\n\n**`createDefaultTemplate()`** -- Returns Template named `\"default\"`:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${data.title} | ${data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>${data.title}</h1>\n    ${data.date ? `<time>${data.date}</time>` : ''}\n    <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**`createListTemplate()`** -- Returns Template named `\"list\"`:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${data.title} | ${data.siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>${data.title}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**Barrel export** (`/workspace/src/core/index.ts`): exports `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types.\n\n---\n\n### 5. All 15 Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`)\n\nHelper functions: `makeFile()` creates a default `ContentFile`, `makePlugin()` creates a default `Plugin`. Both accept partial overrides. Uses `testConfig` with title `\"Test Site\"`, baseUrl `\"https://example.com\"`.\n\n1. **\"registers plugins\"** -- registerPlugin adds to getPlugins() list\n2. **\"registers templates\"** -- registerTemplate makes template available by name\n3. **\"builds with default template and renders HTML\"** -- verifies DOCTYPE, title, content, siteTitle in output\n4. **\"builds with list template and renders list HTML\"** -- verifies list template wraps in `<div class=\"list\">`\n5. **\"outputs raw content when no matching template\"** -- no template registered = raw content passthrough\n6. **\"calls plugin beforeBuild hook\"** -- confirms hook is invoked\n7. **\"calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files\"** -- `.toUpperCase()` transform verified\n8. **\"calls plugin afterBuild hook\"** -- confirms hook is invoked\n9. **\"executes plugins in dependency order\"** -- `b` depends on `a`; order is `[a, b]`\n10. **\"throws on circular dependency\"** -- `a->b->a` throws `\"Circular dependency\"`\n11. **\"throws on missing dependency\"** -- `a` requires `\"missing\"` throws `\"Missing dependency\"`\n12. **\"applies multiple plugins transformContent in order\"** -- `first` then `second` appending text\n13. **\"provides shared data store in build context\"** -- `ctx.data.set/get` works across hooks\n14. **\"retains file metadata through build\"** -- metadata, date, tags survive the build\n15. **\"produces empty output for empty file list\"** -- 0 files = 0 output entries\n\n---\n\n### 6. All Plugin Test Files (60 tests total)\n\n#### 6a. `markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests) -- imports `createMarkdownExtPlugin`\n\n1. **\"converts basic markdown to HTML\"** -- `# Hello` becomes `<h1>`, `**bold**` becomes `<strong>`\n2. **\"handles footnotes with [^1] syntax\"** -- `[^1]` inline becomes `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n3. **\"renders footnote section at bottom\"** -- `[^1]: text` becomes `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>`\n4. **\"converts :::note container to admonition div\"** -- `:::note\\n...\\n:::` becomes `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n5. **\"converts :::warning container\"** -- same pattern with `admonition-warning`\n6. **\"converts :::tip container\"** -- same pattern with `admonition-tip`\n7. **\"preserves existing HTML in content\"** -- already-HTML passes through\n8. **\"handles empty content\"** -- result.content is defined (not undefined/null)\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `transformContent` hook. No dependencies. Must use `marked` library for markdown conversion, plus custom footnote and admonition preprocessing.\n\n#### 6b. `asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests) -- imports `createAssetPipelinePlugin`\n\n1. **\"rewrites relative image URLs to /assets/ path\"** -- `src=\"./image.png\"` becomes `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n2. **\"rewrites relative link URLs\"** -- `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` becomes `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n3. **\"leaves absolute URLs unchanged\"** -- `https://` URLs untouched\n4. **\"generates asset manifest in ctx.data\"** -- `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `{ assets: ['photo.jpg'] }`\n5. **\"handles files with no asset references\"** -- content unchanged\n6. **\"handles multiple assets in one file\"** -- all three filenames in manifest\n7. **\"asset manifest includes all discovered assets\"** -- across multiple files, manifest accumulates\n8. **\"does not double-process already-rewritten URLs\"** -- `/assets/` prefixed URLs left alone, no manifest entry\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `transformContent` hook. No dependencies. Rewrites `src=\"./...\"` and `href=\"./...\"` to `/assets/...`. Stores manifest at `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` as `{ assets: string[] }`.\n\n#### 6c. `syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests) -- imports `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin`\n\n1. **\"adds language class to code blocks\"** -- `class=\"language-javascript\"` becomes `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n2. **\"adds data-language attribute to pre tags\"** -- `<pre>` gets `data-language=\"python\"`\n3. **\"handles multiple code blocks\"** -- both get `data-language`\n4. **\"handles code block with no language\"** -- `<pre><code>plain</code></pre>` unchanged, no `highlighted` class\n5. **\"adds highlighted class\"** -- confirms `highlighted` appears\n6. **\"preserves code block content\"** -- actual code text unchanged\n7. **\"handles empty code blocks\"** -- still gets `data-language` and `highlighted`\n8. **\"does not modify inline code\"** -- `<code>` not inside `<pre>` left alone\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `transformContent` hook. No dependencies. Operates on `<pre><code class=\"language-XXX\">` patterns: adds `highlighted` to class, adds `data-language=\"XXX\"` to `<pre>` tag.\n\n#### 6d. `taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests) -- imports `createTaxonomyPlugin`\n\n1. **\"builds tag index from file tags\"** -- `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` with proper counts\n2. **\"generates tag listing pages\"** -- `ctx.output.has('tags/javascript.html')` with post titles\n3. **\"handles files with no tags\"** -- tagMap.size is 0\n4. **\"handles files with multiple tags\"** -- all 3 tags present in map\n5. **\"tag pages list all files with that tag\"** -- both post titles in tag page HTML\n6. **\"stores tag map in ctx.data\"** -- `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true\n7. **\"handles empty file list\"** -- tagMap.size is 0\n8. **\"tags are case-normalized to lowercase\"** -- `JavaScript` and `JAVASCRIPT` both map to `javascript`\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `beforeBuild` (builds tag index into `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']` as `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`) and `afterBuild` (generates `tags/{tag}.html` pages into `ctx.output`). No dependencies. Case-normalizes tags to lowercase.\n\n#### 6e. `rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests) -- imports `createRssFeedPlugin`\n\n1. **\"generates valid RSS 2.0 XML\"** -- `feed.xml` with `<?xml`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`\n2. **\"feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown\"** -- wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n3. **\"feed items include category tags from taxonomy\"** -- reads `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`, outputs `<category>javascript</category>`\n4. **\"feed includes channel title from config\"** -- `<title>Test Site</title>`\n5. **\"feed items sorted by date newest first\"** -- descending date order\n6. **\"handles files without dates\"** -- title present, no `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>`\n7. **\"feed link uses baseUrl\"** -- `<link>https://example.com</link>` for channel, `<link>https://example.com/post-1.html</link>` for items\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `afterBuild`. Dependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`. Generates `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`. Reads `taxonomy-tags` from `ctx.data` for categories. Sorts items by date descending. Uses CDATA for content.\n\n#### 6f. `search-index.test.ts` (7 tests) -- imports `createSearchIndexPlugin`\n\n1. **\"generates search-index.json in ctx.output\"** -- output key exists\n2. **\"index entries have title, slug, and plain text content\"** -- strips HTML, includes `slug`, `title`, `content`\n3. **\"HTML tags stripped from indexed content\"** -- no `<` or `>` in content field\n4. **\"code blocks included in searchable text\"** -- `const x = 1;` present after stripping\n5. **\"handles empty file list\"** -- returns `[]`\n6. **\"search index is valid JSON\"** -- parses without error, is array, correct length\n7. **\"index entries include tags if present\"** -- `tags: ['js', 'web']` in index entry\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `afterBuild`. Dependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`. Generates `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`. Each entry: `{ slug, title, content (plain text, HTML stripped), tags? }`.\n\n#### 6g. `sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests) -- imports `createSitemapPlugin`\n\n1. **\"generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output\"** -- output key exists\n2. **\"includes all content page URLs\"** -- `https://example.com/post-1.html` for each output entry\n3. **\"includes taxonomy tag page URLs\"** -- reads `taxonomy-tags` from data, includes tag pages\n4. **\"includes feed.xml URL\"** -- if `feed.xml` is in output, it appears in sitemap\n5. **\"URLs use baseUrl from config\"** -- all URLs prefixed with config.baseUrl\n6. **\"sitemap is valid XML structure\"** -- `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`\n7. **\"handles site with no tag pages\"** -- no `/tags/` in sitemap when no taxonomy data\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `afterBuild`. Dependencies: `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`. Generates `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`. Iterates all keys in `ctx.output`, constructs full URLs with baseUrl. Valid XML with `<urlset>` wrapper.\n\n#### 6h. `dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests) -- imports `createDevServerPlugin`\n\n1. **\"stores dev-server-config in ctx.data\"** -- `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` is true\n2. **\"config includes port setting\"** -- port is a number\n3. **\"config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline\"** -- reads `ctx.data['asset-manifest']`, populates `assetPaths` and routes with `handler: 'asset'`\n4. **\"config includes search index path\"** -- if `search-index.json` in output, `searchIndexPath` is `'/search-index.json'`\n5. **\"config includes content routes\"** -- each `.html` output gets a route with `handler: 'static'`\n6. **\"default port is 3000\"** -- `config.port === 3000`\n7. **\"handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\"** -- `assetPaths` defaults to `[]`\n\n**Plugin contract**: Uses `afterBuild`. Dependencies: `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`. Stores config in `ctx.data['dev-server-config']` as:\n```typescript\n{\n  port: number;               // default 3000\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;  // 'static' for HTML, 'asset' for assets\n  assetPaths: string[];       // from asset-manifest\n  searchIndexPath: string;    // '/search-index.json' if present\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Package & Config Summary\n\n**`package.json`**:\n- Name: `bench-ssg-toolkit`, version `1.0.0`, type `\"module\"` (ESM)\n- Scripts: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint src/ tests/), `test` (vitest